# What does this all mean?

Together, these visuals suggest that GDP status may be related to dominant plastic waste type, but the relationship is not perfectly clear or consistent. “Other” plastic and PET appear most often as dominant categories, while the GDP-group and flow charts show that countries from different economic groups still overlap across several plastic types. Regionally, Asia has the highest total plastic waste, but the per-capita comparison shows that total waste counts are strongly influenced by population size and regional representation, so GDP alone cannot fully explain plastic waste patterns.
:::

